{"kind":"symbol","schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"metadata":{"fragments":[{"text":"overlayBounds","kind":"identifier"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"overlayBounds"}],"symbolKind":"property","externalID":"c:objc(pl)MLNOverlay(py)overlayBounds","title":"overlayBounds","modules":[{"name":"MapLibre"}],"roleHeading":"Instance Property","role":"symbol"},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The cooordinate rectangle that encompasses the overlay. (required) (read-only)"}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"languages":["occ"],"platforms":["iOS"],"tokens":[{"text":"@property","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" (","kind":"text"},{"text":"nonatomic","kind":"keyword"},{"text":", ","kind":"text"},{"text":"readonly","kind":"keyword"},{"text":") ","kind":"text"},{"text":"MLNCoordinateBounds","kind":"typeIdentifier","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNCoordinateBounds","preciseIdentifier":"c:@S@MLNCoordinateBounds"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"overlayBounds","kind":"identifier"},{"text":";","kind":"text"}]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"discussion","text":"Discussion"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"This property contains the smallest rectangle that completely encompasses the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"overlay. Implementers of this protocol must set this area when implementing","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"their overlay class, and after setting it, you must not change it.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"If this overlay spans the antimeridian, its bounds may extend west of −180 degrees","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"longitude or east of 180 degrees longitude. For example, an overlay covering the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Pacific Ocean from Tokyo to San Francisco might have a bounds extending","type":"text"},{